course_metadata.title: INVESTMENT FOR HOUSING DECARBONISATION AND ENERGY MANAGEMENT. FINANCIAL DIGITAL TOOLS FOR ANALYSIS AND DECISION MAKING ON AFFORDABLE HOUSING

content_chunks.content: The European Green Deal is the EU's growth and recovery strategy that aims to transform Europe into the first climate-neutral bloc by 2050. Energy efficiency is a key area of action, without which the full decarbonisation of the EU economy cannot be achieved. Within this context, energy efficiency investments need to be increased in all sectors of the economy. This is the most cost-effective and sustainable way towards climate neutrality. The decarbonisation of the housing stock will make it safer, more affordable and accessible. The study course provides knowledge about the housing decarbonisation and energy management, its basics, different aspects, energy efficiency measures, benefits, problems and improvement possibilities in the building sector, the role of local authorities in energy efficiency issues, as well as financial instruments to support energy efficient projects.

Technology for housing decarbonization investment and energy management financing - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in housing decarbonization investment and European Green Deal financing using advanced energy efficiency financial instruments and EU funding mechanisms. Students will master structural fund applications, local authority energy programs, and municipal energy efficiency support for optimal international decarbonization experience and building energy certification implementation. The curriculum focuses on practical residential energy standards development, non-residential energy standards establishment, and energy efficiency cost-benefit analysis for comprehensive technical solution development and building renovation management. Participants will gain hands-on experience with decarbonization education programs, energy policy development, and housing management competencies for effective financial decision-making tools and affordable housing investment strategies. The program emphasizes interdisciplinary approaches to energy efficiency in housing management, covering technical, political, social, and environmental aspects for comprehensive housing sector decarbonization.
